ExtornoTechs V-RAXTOR v1.3.7.205





V-RAXTOR is a software solution for audio plug-in hosting in a versatile and intuitive racks battery, connected to a multi-channel virtual mixer.

High operation flexibility and total control over plug-in interconnection enable users to implement a consistent audio-stream processing system.

IDE-style workspace with direct manipulation emphasis offers new step of naturality to the human/software interaction process.

Modern pseudo-3D graphical interface with shadows, highlights, relief-mapping and smooth animation produces a realistic virtual studio representation.


Popular technologies support makes it easier to utilize today's software/hardware solutions:

   Plug-in interfaces Ã¢â‚¬â€œ VST2, VST3 or ReWire (fast rescan);
   Audio interface Ã¢â‚¬â€œ ASIO or DirectSound;
   Graphic interface Ã¢â‚¬â€œ Direct3D or OpenGL;
   Standardized MIDI-protocol for virtual studio control.

V-RAXTOR architecture foundation stones are described below:

VIRTUAL DEVICE (PLUG-IN)

Basic system metaphor. It is the actual plug-in &quot;container&quot;:

   Plug-in Volume level control;
   Plug-in Pan level control;
   Plug-in Dry/Wet (Mix) level control;
   Plug-in Program selector;
   Plug-in Editor display button;
   Plug-in L/R-channel volume indicators.

VIRTUAL DEVICE RACK

Device &quot;container&quot;. It is used for mounting multiple Devices in a stack manner:

   Input module;
   Unlimited number of Devices as FX-chain &quot;links&quot;;
   Output module;
   Free in-rack Device reposition.

VIRTUAL RACKS BATTERY

Racks &quot;container&quot;. It is used for multiple Racks aggregation in a battery manner:

   32 separate Racks;
   Free cross-rack Device reposition;
   Gesture navigation between Racks.

VIRTUAL MIXER

Battery signals routing and control unit. It is used for mixing, switching, changing the levels of audio-streams and so on:

   32 separate mixer Channels;
   Volume level control;
   Pan level control;
   Send level control;
   Mute-switcher;
   Solo-switcher;
   FX on/off-switcher;
   Input (Left or Right) audio channel selector;
   L/R-channel volume indicators.

USER PLUG-INS LIST AT HAND

Provides fast access to the audio plug-ins, installed on the user's machine:

   DXi (under development);
   VST2;
   VST3;
   ReWire;
   V-RAXTOR plug-ins (under development).

PROGRAM ASSETS BROWSER

Provides fast access to the program assets, stored by user:

   Stored Projects;
   Stored Devices;
   Stored Racks;
   Stored Mixer States;
   Stored Workspaces.


System Requirements

1 GHz CPU, 512 MB RAM, 20 MB HDD, DirectSound/ASIO-compatible audio interface, OpenGL3.3/Direct3D10/11

Supported Sample Formats (loads or saves) include
FLAC, MP3, OGG, WAV


Installation

1.Uninstall previous versions.
2.Install V-RAXTOR.
3.Copy R2RVRAX.dll to the installation dir.
4.Run our EmuTool.
5.Patch V-Raxtor.exe.
6.Generate License Key.
7.Run V-RAXTOR and activate.
 You can activate from Help -&gt; About.



